# This file ensures the Migrations folder is tracked in Git version control.
# 
# The folder is intentionally empty as EF Core migration files are auto-generated
# when running 'dotnet ef migrations add <MigrationName>' commands.
#
# MIGRATION: This folder replaces the legacy SqlDataProvider database migration approach
# with EF Core Code-First migrations. Each migration file will contain:
#   - Up() method: Apply schema changes (CREATE, ALTER, INSERT, etc.)
#   - Down() method: Revert schema changes for rollback capability
#
# Usage:
#   dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate -p src/DnnMigration.Infrastructure -s src/DnnMigration.Api
#   dotnet ef database update -p src/DnnMigration.Infrastructure -s src/DnnMigration.Api
#
# Note: Migration files will be timestamped and named like:
#   20240101120000_InitialCreate.cs
#   20240101120000_InitialCreate.Designer.cs
#   DnnDbContextModelSnapshot.cs
